(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Berlin &ndash; Police in Germany say the attempted abduction of a newborn child was foiled by the quick reaction of his 9-year-old brother.Hamburg police say a 34-year-old German woman had taken the baby from a hospital room on Friday afternoon, while the mother was sleeping.The brother followed the unnamed woman and talked to her, whereupon she handed the day-old child back. She was arrested and taken to a psychiatric clinic.Police spokesman Ulf Wundrack said on Monday that the boy's actions contributed "significantly" to the baby's return.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.